  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Pat your <strong>pork belly </strong>dry with kitchen paper, then<strong> </strong>score the<strong> fatty side </strong>in a criss-cross pattern by drawing a sharp knife through the skin, deep enough to reach the meat below</p><p>Season with<strong> </strong>a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and rub it deep into the criss-cross pattern</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708422717128-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708422717128-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708422717128-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708422717128-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1708422717128-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Flip the <strong>scored pork</strong> over and rub your<strong> Dijon mustard</strong> all over the non-fatty side with your <strong>dried sage </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708422723217-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708422723217-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708422723217-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708422723217-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1708422723217-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut 2 pieces of<strong> tin foil</strong> approx. the size of A4 paper and lay the<strong> pork</strong> (fatty-side up), in the middle of the foil, (doubling it up prevents any leakages!)</p><p>Loosely scrunch the edges of the foil around the pork leaving the skin exposed and transfer the parcel[s] to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Pour 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[110ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>around the pork</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 30 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708422729170-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708422729170-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708422729170-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708422729170-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1708422729170-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>potatoes</strong>, then chop in half</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced carrot </strong>and <strong>halved potatoes </strong>to a large heat-proof bowl covered with<strong> cling film</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 5-8 min or until slightly tender, then remove the cling film and set aside</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1708422734589-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1708422734589-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1708422734589-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1708422734589-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1708422734589-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide your<strong> sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) and shape into 3 stuffing meatballs per person</p><p>Once the pork has had 30 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>carrot </strong>and <strong>potatoes</strong> (reserve the bowl!) with the <strong>stuffing meatballs </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 18-20 min or until the<strong> </strong>pork belly skin is crisp and tender and the sausage stuffing is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1708422740688-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1708422740688-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1708422740688-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1708422740688-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1708422740688-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach </strong>and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once the pork is ready, remove the tray[s] from the oven and transfer the <strong>roasted pork belly </strong>to a clean chopping board to rest for 2-3 min</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the tray[s] and combine with the <strong>roasted carrot</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for 2-3 min or until the spinach is wilted</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1708422746936-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1708422746936-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1708422746936-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1708422746936-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1708422746936-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything is nearly ready, boil a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>gravy paste </strong>with 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>in the reserved bowl, whisk thoroughly</p><p>Put it in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 30-40 secs or until thickened and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1708422751740-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
